annotation.TEXT: Hmm... And since one of them is a power up, I may as well take an intentional hit that won't actually cost me anything in order to hit the fourth ? block.
Whoa, that was close!
Huh. The game's now requiring me to bullet jump. It's simple enough here, but I'm wondering just how tricky the game could get with this later...
Oh, man! It's a starman, man!
Huh, so that's it for this world for now I guess. I can't seem to move anywhere else here right now.
Huh? How do I get past this? ...Ohh... How clever! Once you think "L button", it's pretty simple, though the tree trunk does obscure your visibility, so be careful of that.
Oh, man! This pipe goes somewhere!
Whoa, man! Well, you know I've gotta check every pipe!

Aww... Too bad the enemies are all cheapskate Chucks, which for some reason, are always worth 800 points when star-killed, and don't contribute to a combo.

Alright, there's only one place left for me to go to: 1-5, "Iggy's Vine Castle". But, how many vines could it possibly have? Find out next time! To be continued...
And now to check every turn block, even though this is probably a big waste of time...
